<br>
Don't bring other people into this argument. Magesthink is his own person, he is not the other people you mentioned. Keep your comments on the person in question, comparing him/her to other people is a waste of time and isn't nice to the people you associate him with.<br>
<br>
Magesthink,<br>
<br>
Hi, I r tard. I r comparing 6 people 60 to 1 enchanter &gt; 60. OMG chanter can compete effectively... weird.<br>
<br>
Charm is a fantastic tool for chanters. But the notion that it is going to replace mages for xp groups is downright stupid. If it gets to the point where Chanters are more needed than mages for their pets, charm will be nerfed, simple as that.<br>
<br>
Go away, sir. 5 Mage pets + slower = sweet xp. <br>
<br>
My actual advice to the practitioners of these groups, however, is to not waste time healing pets.  I haven't seen Lobaner around here recently, but, I hate to let you know guy, you are disposable.  Chaining pets is ALWAYS more mana efficient than healing them. The DPS contributed by Mask + Swords + Belt + BO5 2 nukes for the same mana. Let him die, make a new one.<br>
<br>
This is ENTIRELY wrong for the epic, however. He is not disposable, simply because of the 5 min or whatever recast. Since I got 61 + 62 pets, I never use him. Keep grinding away and as soon as you get 61 for that crew, 5 mages + shaman/bard/chanter = teh pwn.<br>
<br>
Tarqal of Xev <br>
