<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
This was the Mage group Vs PoG.  After clearing the protectors and killing Treah, we spent a few hours clearning the rest of the zone.  At one point we had 5 mobs on our group.  They died, we lived, it rocked.<br>
<br>
I did some calculations on the fight at the end of this post. I did not step into melee range as I was trying to have a small log to look at. Based on that, I assumed what the average pet damage was but I'm pretty confident on what it would be. Next time we do this, I'll get in melee range and parse out the pet damage too. I only have my nuke damage calculated on this, I wish I could see all the group members nuke/dot damage =P. <br>
<br>
This was a long fight, nearly 7 minutes. So it's a good way to look at sustained mage damage over that time period. It's not totally sutained though, but I was nuking pretty much nonstop with only switching to click nukes for 3 nukes out of 28 that landed. I started the fight around 90? and ended too low to cast one more nuke.<br>
<br>
We have killed Treah with 1 mage heavy group 3 times now. 1st time she dropped a Warrior BP, last time a Shaman BP, and this time a Beastlord BP.<br>
<br>
