At any rate, I do not want this thread moved to rants, so back on topic:<br>
<br>
Pet groups rock, and always have.  Some of my most fun (and profitable) experiences in any era have been chain pulling for a handful of mages and necros.  Pull, slow, sic charm pet, wait for mage pet to gain aggro (or root if earth pet), run out to park another mob next to the pets, so the crowd of Jabobers never stops eating.  These groups have zero downtime, low risk (virtually no risk, really, if you forego the charm pet), and fast experience.  They are a little harder to assemble and pull off in PoP, but still very doable, and very profitable.  More to the point, these groups are FUN!<br>
